	volume = {72},
	issn = {1882-3351},
	abstract = {Embryo culture was utilized to obtain progenies from crosses between three diploid, female rootstock cultivars, `Millardet et de Grasset 101-14' ['101-14' (2x), Vitis riparia Michx X V. rupestris Scheele], `Millardet et de Grasset 41B' ['41B' (2x), V. berlandieri Planch. X V. vinifera L.] and `Kober 5BB' ['5BB' (2x), V. berlandieri X V. riparia] and a tetraploid male rootstock cultivar `Teleki 5C', ['5C' (4x), V. berlandieri X V. riparia]. Most of the embryos derived from these three cross combinations had globular and abnormal- or obscure-shapes. Four, three and two triploids were obtained from the embryos derived from `101-14' (2x) x `5C' (4x), `41B' (2x) X `5C' (4x) and `5BB' (2x) X `5C' (4x), respectively. The growth characteristics of a triploid derived from `5BB' (2x) X `5C' (4x), called E-1 (3x) were compared with `5BB' (2x) and its tetraploid ['5BB' (4x)] in the acclimating stage. Shoot and root growth; and leaf morphology of E -1 (3x) were intermediate between those of `5BB' (2x) and `5BB' (4x). The growth of `Kyoho' (V. x labruscana Bailey) grapevines micrografted onto `5BB' (2x), E-1 (3x) and `5BB' (4x) were also compared in the acclimating stage. The growth of scion shoot and root was the largest on `5BB' (2x), intermediate on E-1 (3x) and the smallest `5BB' (4x). In the aseptic co-culture of root segments and phylloxera (Daktulosphaira vitifoliae Fitch), E-1 (3x) and `5BB' (4x) was found to be highly resistant to the insect.},
